  "prompt": "Is it ok to spend the night with my fianc\u00e9 or does it go against God?",
  "response": "The question of whether spending the night with your fianc\u00e9 goes against God's teachings can depend on various factors, including your personal beliefs, the teachings of your faith, and the cultural context you find yourself in. \n\nIn many religious traditions, particularly in conservative or orthodox interpretations of Christianity, premarital cohabitation or spending the night together may be viewed as inappropriate due to beliefs about chastity and the sanctity of marriage. \n\nHowever, other interpretations of faith may emphasize the importance of love, commitment, and the intent to marry, suggesting that it is acceptable for engaged couples to spend time together in a close and intimate setting. \n\nUltimately, this decision is a personal one. You may want to consider your own beliefs, discuss it with your fianc\u00e9, and perhaps seek counsel from a trusted spiritual leader or advisor if you're unsure. It's important that both partners are aligned in their values and decisions regarding their relationship.",
